	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Starting at <strong>6th level</strong>, the nature of your benefactor shines out from your deeds. You gain two benefits to your @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.17XzNXQouNiyoVuD]{Inspiring Icon} feature that best reflect the nature of your benefactor. Choose two of the following, these choices cannot be changed once chosen.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Artifice.</strong> Inspired creatures gain a +1 bonus to their AC until the end of your next turn.</p></li><li><p><strong>Chaos.</strong> The expertise die increases to 1d6, but on results of 3 or less, it applies a penalty instead of a bonus. For example, an expertise die roll of 2 subtracts 2 from the result.</p></li><li><p><strong>Darkness.</strong> Inspired creatures gain <em>darkvision</em> with a range of 120 feet for the duration.</p></li><li><p><strong>Death.</strong> The expertise die increases to 1d6 for attacks made against bloodied creatures.</p></li><li><p><strong>Earth.</strong> Inspired creatures cannot be shoved, pushed, or knocked prone for the duration.</p></li><li><p><strong>Evil.</strong> The expertise die increases to 1d6 for Deception and Persuasion checks.</p></li><li><p><strong>Fire.</strong> Inspired creatures deal an amount of additional fire damage to up to one target equal to the expertise die when rolled on an attack.</p></li><li><p><strong>Good.</strong> Creatures that attempt to target inspired creatures with an attack must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save creatures cannot follow through with their attack and must select a new target if able or the attack is wasted. Once a creature successfully saves against this effect, they are immune to it for the next 24 hours.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ice.</strong> Inspired creatures deal an amount of additional cold damage to up to one target equal to the expertise die when rolled on an attack.</p></li><li><p><strong>Knowledge.</strong> The expertise die increases to 1d6 for Culture, History, Medicine, and Religion checks.</p></li><li><p><strong>Law.</strong> Inspired creatures may reroll up to one failed saving throw made during the duration.</p></li><li><p><strong>Life.</strong> Inspired creatures regain a number of lost hit points equal to 1d4 + your Charisma modifier.</p></li><li><p><strong>Light.</strong> Enemy creatures in the radius must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save creatures become magically illuminated until the start of your next turn as per the spell faerie fire.</p></li><li><p><strong>Love.</strong> Inspired creatures gain a 10-foot movement speed bonus when moving closer to allies.</p></li><li><p><strong>Magic.</strong> The expertise die increases to 1d6 when rolled for magic attacks, Arcana checks, and saving throws against magic.</p></li><li><p><strong>Nature.</strong> Inspired creatures are reinvigorated and gain 1d6 temporary hit points. In addition, the expertise die increases to 1d6 for Nature checks.</p></li><li><p><strong>Sea.</strong> Inspired creatures move with fluid grace and ignore attacks of opportunity.</p></li><li><p><strong>Sky.</strong> Inspired creatures are surrounding winds for the duration, and gain a +2 AC bonus against ranged weapon attacks for the duration.</p></li><li><p><strong>Undeath.</strong> The expertise die increases to 1d6 for death saving throws.</p></li><li><p><strong>War.</strong> The expertise die increases to 1d6 for attacks made using martial and exotic weapons.</p></li></ul>",
